            "text": "streusel"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is the point of this cake. It should be rubbed until it clumps into pieces the size of small grapes; too finely rubbed and it compacts during baking into a dry layer instead of a crunchy one. The soured cream in the batter keeps the sponge moist enough to stand up to the dense topping."
          }
        ]
